<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-10-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="202" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5315/563.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-10-27"><hi rend="italic">October 27,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Fletcher reports that both the German minister and the German
                            bankers’ representative seem favorable to the solution proposed by him
                            yesterday, namely, the construction of section Hsiangyang to Kuangshui
                            under American engineers, and promise to recommend it to Berlin. He adds
                            that the British are favorable also, and that all recognize danger of
                            delay.</p>
